In a #bowl{}, combine @Breadcrumbs{1%pack}, @Mexican Style Spice Mix{2%sachets} and @salt{to taste}.

Thinly slice the @Irish Chicken Breast{320%grams} lengthways into strips (5-6 per breast).

Season the chicken with salt and @Pepper{to taste} and coat well with @Mayo{2%sachets}. Dip the strips into the breadcrumbs, ensuring they're well coated.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Place a large pan over high heat and add enough @Oil{to taste} to cover the base.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden-brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Turn every ~{2-3%minutes} and adjust the heat if necessary.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Serve the warm mini goujons with @Aioli{1%sachet} and @Ketchup{2%sachets} on the side.